tatami.core.util.graph

Class Graph

  • java.lang.Object
    • tatami.core.util.logging.Unit
      • tatami.core.util.graph.Graph
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    GraphPattern

    public class Graph
extends Unit

    Represents a directed graph. Subclasses: Node and Edge.

    Functions that modify the graph return the graph itself, so that chained calls are possible.

    This class should only be used as a data structure. Visualization should happen elsewhere (for instance, in LinearGraphRepresentation.

    Currently only supports adding of new nodes and edges.

    Warning: if a graph contains the edge, id does not necessarily contain any of the nodes of the edge. It may be that the nodes have not been added to the graph. This is because this graph may be a subgraph of a larger graph.

    Author:
    Andrei Olaru
